<paragraph pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia peltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">
<pageBreakToken pageId="207" pageNumber="208" start="start">Conostegia</pageBreakToken>
peltata
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Cerro Jefe endemic quite distinctive because of its peltate leaves. It is closely related to another Cerro Jefe endemic, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jefensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia jefensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Gleason" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia consimilis" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia trichosantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia trichosantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares the mostly linear-oblong petals with these species. With these particular petals, this clade is convergent with other taxa in section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Almeda &amp; Umana" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia friedmaniorum" order="Myrtales" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friedmaniorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="207" pageNumber="208">Conostegia friedmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
